   324→        <p><b>Not-Wikipedia</b> is a theoretical concept and <a href="/wiki/Digital_artifact">digital artifact</a> describing an entity that possesses the visual characteristics of <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia">Wikipedia</a> but lacks the underlying database, server infrastructure, or collaborative community. While appearing identical to the popular online encyclopedia, Not-Wikipedia functions as a "shell" or a "facade."<sup><a href="#cite1">[1]</a></sup></p>
   325→        
   326→        <p>The concept is often used in computer science education to demonstrate <a href="/wiki/Front-end_web_development">front-end web development</a>, specifically the replication of <a href="/wiki/Cascading_Style_Sheets">cascading style sheets</a> (CSS) without back-end functionality.</p>
